{{update|date=October 2018}} '''[[Evolve Wrestling]]''' is an [[United States Of Amerca|American]] [[professional wrestling promotion]] which was founded in 2010 by former [[Ring of Honor]] booker and [[Dragon Gate USA]] vice president, [[Gabe Sapolsky]]. Over the course since, it has held 11 [[House show|live events]] and 90 internet [[pay-per-view]]s.
==''EVOLVE 1: Richards vs. Ibushi''== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=EVOLVE 1: Richards vs. Ibushi |promotion=Evolve Wrestling |date=January 1, 2010 |venue=Rahway Rec Center |city=[[Rahway, New Jersey]] |attendance=ca. 500 }} The inaugural EVOLVE show, '''EVOLVE 1: Richards vs. Ibushi''', was held in [[Rahway, New Jersey]] at the Rahway Rec Center. Lenny Leonard and Leonard F. Chikarason served as the commentators. In the main event, Davey Richards, accompanied by Kyle O'Reilly and Tony Kozina, faced against Kota Ibushi, who was accompanied by Michael Nakazawa.
