A '''Non-Equity''' theater company or [[Stagecraft|theater production]] is produced and performed by personnel who are not members of the [[Actors' Equity Association|Actors Equity Association]] Union. Non-Equity theaters tend to be small "storefront" theaters that may mount productions infrequently or rely heavily on non-professional actors and production staff.

