'''''The Be Bold Show''''' ('''''B'''''ringing '''''E'''''ducation and '''''B'''''uilding '''''O'''''pportunities for '''''L'''''eadership and '''''D'''''evelopment. Show) is a [[Ghana]]ian [[television]] [[talk show]] hosted and created by [[Christal Jeanne|Christal Beeko]] and [[Sterre Mkatini]]. It was launched in 2011 and is aired on e.tv on Saturdays at 9pm with a repeat on Thursdays 1.30pm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Show Time Change|url=http://thebeboldshow.com/about-us/press/142-be-bold-showtime-change|publisher=The Be Bold show|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=e.tv Launches Be Bold Talk Show|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=201211|publisher=Ghana Web|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref>
The show features innovative young people and celebrities contributing positively to Africa. Some popular guests and projects on the show in the past seasons were Christie Brown, Heel The World, [[Kwaku Sintim-Misa]], [[Ameyaw Debrah]], Trashy Bags, Honourable [[Hanna Tetteh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Guest Directory|url=http://thebeboldshow.com/guest-directory|publisher=The Be Bold Show|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref>
The show is also known to facilitate the KBG BEBOLD Scholarship Fund, and by the team efforts of The Be Bold Show dedicated employees in the names Afua Rida, Reginald Adjei, Mabanga Chisenga, Efua Acquaah Harrison, Quincy Dwamena, William Kweku Asamoah and Victor Toboh, was a huge success. .<ref>{{cite web|title=The Be Bold KBG Scholarship Fund, Get Involved|url=http://www.etvghana.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3407:the-be-bold-kbg-scholarship-fund-get-involved|publisher=Etv Ghana|accessdate=18 August 2013}}</ref>
